{"word":"ἐπόρνυμι","slug":"ἐπόρνυμι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπόρνυμι</b></el> <el>(and <el>-ύω</el>) (<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-όρσω</el>) (aor1 <el>-ῶρσα</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to stir up, arouse, excite</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to rouse and send against</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <el>ὕπνον ἐπῶρσε</el> <i>sent</i> sleep <i>upon</i> her, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <el>ἐπόρνῠμαι</el>, with perf2 <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <el>ἐπόρωρα</el>, 3rd sg. epic aor2 <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <el>ἐπῶρτο</el>: — <i>to rise against, assault, fly upon</i> one, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>:—of things, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}